text.section:
The purposes of the Exchange are to:
reduce the number of uninsured in the State;
facilitate the purchase and sale of qualified health plans in the individual market in the State by providing a transparent marketplace;
assist qualified employers in the State in facilitating the enrollment of their employees in qualified health plans in the small group market in the State and in accessing small business tax credits;
assist individuals in accessing public programs, premium tax credits, and cost-sharing reductions; and
supplement the individual and small group insurance markets outside of the Exchange.
